other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast

findings.pleural_effusion: Bilateral small pleural effusions, right greater than left, with associated compressive atelectasis.
findings.liver: Enhances homogeneously without focal lesion or intrahepatic biliary duct dilation.
findings.gallbladder: Demonstrates no stone, wall thickening or edema, or pericholecystic fluid.
findings.pancreas: Enlarged and edematous, with surrounding fat stranding and trace free fluid.
findings.pancreatic_duct: At the upper limits of normal, measuring 3 mm, with no obstructing stone or mass.
findings.kidneys: Symmetric nephrograms with a 1.8 cm simple cyst in the right kidney.
findings.GI: Small and large bowel within normal limits.
findings.os_seous_structures: Multilevel degenerative changes of the thoracolumbar spine.
